LARDD 1
TITLE Keplet Distribution
TEXT Keplet is the LardOS CLI/DOS productivity distribution.
TEXT It is built for mode switching, visible macros, and keyboard-first work.
SECTION Identity
ITEM Branch: keplet
ITEM Version line: v3.0.0b-keplet
ITEM Channel: beta, because this is a new distribution surface.
ITEM Base: main LardOS features are preserved instead of removed.
SECTION Workflow
ITEM keplet on enters the KEPLET[mode] prompt.
ITEM keplet mode dos keeps DOS-style commands close at hand.
ITEM keplet mode nav adds l/r/m/g/b for list/read/more/go/back navigation.
ITEM keplet mode edit adds w/a/n for write/append/notes.
ITEM keplet mode macro runs saved macro names directly.
ITEM keplet mode lsh lets normal Lard Shell commands pass through first.
SECTION Macros
ITEM macro list shows visible shortcuts from keplet.lardd.
ITEM macro set name command writes a shortcut the user can edit later.
ITEM macro run name args runs the shortcut and appends extra args.
ITEM macro delete name removes the macro definition from keplet.lardd.
ITEM macro explain name says exactly what the macro expands to.
SECTION Values
ITEM Keplet does not hide automation; keplet.lardd is writable and inspectable.
ITEM Keplet keeps GUI, RXE, SYSRXE, KMO, SUM, media, recovery, and raw-control paths.
ITEM The distribution changes the default work style, not the user's ownership.
END
